        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 61 of a 12-week money program. The script targets the clinging pattern: the sense that money once gone is gone for good, that a dry spell is always around the corner, that the responsible thing is to hold on tight rather than trust replenishment. The reframe moves toward money as something that always comes back.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to tapping? Read ",
